title: [West Docks, Dreamstone Pier]
description: A glaes-accented oak docking structure rises from the water with five piers jutting out in orderly fashion to provide numerous points of portage.  Every docking slip sports thick, canvas-wrapped cork bumpers and a dozen buoys painted with golden helms.  An oak sign strung between thick strands of hemp railing reads, "West Docks, Dreamstone Pier - Slips 21-25."  A severed kiramon mandible is haphazardly nailed to the bottom of the sign.
